Target: The Building Structure ontology (OntoBuildingStructure) is an ontology developed to represent the building structural components (walls, doors, slabs, roofs, stairs) and their individual characteristics such as dimensions and qualities.

Comment: The visible surface of a building's roof at aerial view. It can comprise of several roofs.
Label: Roof Facade

Comment: The frontage  of a building. It can comprise of several walls.
Label: Wall Facade

Comment: The northern frontage  of a building. It can comprise of several walls.
Label: North Wall Facade

Comment: The easthern frontage  of a building. It can comprise of several walls.
Label: East Wall Facade

Comment: The southern frontage  of a building. It can comprise of several walls.
Label: South Wall Facade

Comment: The westhern frontage  of a building. It can comprise of several walls.
Label: West Wall Facade

Comment: An abstract class defining the attached construction parts of a building that constitute the building, such as walls, built-in partitions, roofs, doors, and columns. Generally, the building and all of its structural components are treated as a whole when the building is acquired, constructed, reconstructed, or erected and first placed in service.
Label: Building Structure Component

Comment: A vertical load-bearing structural member that is designed to support and transmit the load of the slab on the higher floors to the foundation through compression.
Label: Column

Comment: Upper interior surface component of any space in a construction, building, or infrastructure.
Label: Ceiling

Comment: Construction enclosing the building from above.
Label: Roof

Comment: Roof with a slope angle that is less than 9.46 degree.
Label: Flat Roof

Comment: Roof with a slope angle that is greater than or equal to 9.46 degree.
Label: Inclined Roof

Comment: Lower support component of any space in a construction, building, or infrastructure. It include a slab and flooring finish.
Label: Floor

Comment: A building structure component that is composed of at least two other components, including assemblies. For example, a wall is an assembly that can consist of a door or window.
Label: Assembly

Comment: Vertical construction usually in masonry or in concrete which bounds or subdivides a construction works and fulfills a load bearing or retaining function. It is also an assembly that can host doors and windows.
Label: Wall

Comment: Construction for closing a vertical or near vertical opening in a wall or pitched roof that will admit light and may admit fresh air.
Label: Window

Comment: Construction for closing an opening, intended primarily for access with hinged, pivoted or sliding operation.
Label: Door

Comment: Construction comprising a succession of horizontal stages (steps or landings) that make it possible to pass on foot to other levels. It can be treater as an assembly consisting of the following types: stair flights, railings, landings, and stair structural components.
Label: Stair

Comment: An assembly of building components in a single "run" of stair steps that are not interrupted by a landing.
Label: Stair Flight

Comment: A floor section that is connected to one or more stair flights or ramp flights.
Label: Landing

Comment: A frame assembly that is adjacent to human circulation spaces and at some space boundaries, in which it is used in lieu of walls or to complement walls. It is usually designed to aid humans, either as an optional physical support, or to prevent injury by falling.
Label: Railing

Comment: A structural member designed to carry loads between or beyond points of support for a staircase.
Label: Stair Structural Component

Comment: The size of the roof on a building
Label: Roof Area

Comment: The size of the roof area of a building that is suitable for solar use.
Label: Solar Suitable Roof Area

Comment: The total size of the roof of a building.
Label: Total Roof Area

Comment: Links any entity to a specific quantity defined in the OM ontology. This relationship is not intended to be stated explicitly, but inferred from its sub-properties. For application, only the sub-properties are used.
Label: has quantity

Comment: A relationship between the roof of a building and the area it covers.
Label: has area of

Comment: A relationship between a roof and its angle/position relative to the Sun.
Label: has orientation

Comment: A relationship between a roof and its slope angle.
Label: has slope

Comment: A relation that links a building to their roof and wall facades.
Label: has facade

Comment: A relation between a facade and its comprising components. Each facade comprises of one or more instances of their coresponding component type, such as a roof or a wall.
Label: comprises of

Comment: A relation between a facade and its comprising components. Each facade comprises of one or more instances of their corresponding component type, such as a roof or a wall.
Label: comprises of

Comment: A relation between a facade and its comprising components. Each facade comprises of one or more instances of their corresponding component type, such as a roof or a wall.
Label: comprises of

Range: Landing UNION Railing UNION StairFlight UNION StairStructuralComponent UNION Door UNION Window
Comment: A relation between a facade and its comprising components. Each facade comprises of one or more instances of their corresponding component type, such as a roof or a wall.
Label: consists of

Range: Landing UNION Railing UNION StairFlight UNION StairStructuralComponent
Comment: A relationship that denotes the subcomposition of an assembly with their individual components. An example is that stairs consists of railing, landing, stair flights, and stair structural components.
Label: consists of

Comment: A relationship that denotes the subcomposition of an assembly with their individual components. An example is that stairs consists of railing, landing, stair flights, and stair structural components.
Label: consists of

Comment: Defines the number of risers on a stair flight.
Label: has number of risers

Comment: Defines the number of treads on a stair flight.
Label: has number of treads

Comment: Defines the height of each riser on a stair flight.
Label: has riser height

Comment: Defines the length of each tread on a stair flight.
Label: has tread length

Comment: A Boolean indicator that is true when the roof is suitable for installation of heat support, and is false, otherwise.
Label: is heat support suitable

Comment: A Boolean indicator that is true when the roof is suitable for installation of photovoltaic panels, and is false, otherwise.
Label: is pv panel suitable

Comment: A Boolean indicator that is true when the roof is suitable for installation of solar collectors, and is false, otherwise.
Label: is solar collector suitable
